201	### Severity Boxes Row
202	```css
203	.severity-boxes-row {
204	    display: flex;
205	    gap: 8px;
206	    margin: 0; /* Remove margins - padding is handled by parent */
207	    padding: 0 0 10px 0; /* Bottom padding for shadow space */
208	    justify-content: flex-start; /* Align boxes to start */
209	}
210	```
211	
212	### Adjacent Component Adjustment
213	```css
214	/* Move violation details up when severity is collapsed */
215	.severity-summary-component.collapsed + .violation-details-component {
216	    margin-top: -16px; /* Adjust spacing when severity is collapsed */
217	}
218	```
219	
220	## JavaScript Implementation
221	
222	```javascript
223	// Severity Summary toggle functionality (new) - Two button approach
224	const severitySummaryToggleExpanded = document.querySelector('.severity-summary-toggle-expanded');
225	const severitySummaryToggleCollapsed = document.querySelector('.severity-summary-toggle-collapsed');
226	const severitySummaryContainer = document.querySelector('.severity-summary-component');
227	const severitySummaryLabel = document.querySelector('.severity-summary-collapsed-label');
228	
229	if (severitySummaryContainer) {
230	    const toggleSeveritySummary = () => {
231	        // Toggle collapsed class
232	        severitySummaryContainer.classList.toggle('collapsed');
233	        
234	        // Update aria-expanded on both buttons
235	        const isCollapsed = severitySummaryContainer.classList.contains('collapsed');
236	        if (severitySummaryToggleExpanded) {
237	            severitySummaryToggleExpanded.setAttribute('aria-expanded', !isCollapsed);
238	        }
239	        if (severitySummaryToggleCollapsed) {
240	            severitySummaryToggleCollapsed.setAttribute('aria-expanded', !isCollapsed);
241	        }
242	        
243	        // CSS handles button visibility - no icon switching needed
244	        
245	        // Announce state change for accessibility
246	        const announcement = isCollapsed ? 'Severity summary collapsed' : 'Severity summary expanded';
247	        this.announce(announcement);
248	    };
249	    
250	    // Add click events to both toggle buttons
251	    if (severitySummaryToggleExpanded) {
252	        severitySummaryToggleExpanded.addEventListener('click', toggleSeveritySummary);
253	    }
254	    if (severitySummaryToggleCollapsed) {
255	        severitySummaryToggleCollapsed.addEventListener('click', toggleSeveritySummary);
256	    }
257	    
258	    // Add click event to collapsed label
259	    if (severitySummaryLabel) {
260	        severitySummaryLabel.addEventListener('click', toggleSeveritySummary);
261	    }
262	}
263	```
264	
265	## Key Implementation Points
266	
267	### 1. Two-Button Approach
268	- **NO icon switching in JavaScript** - CSS handles visibility
269	- Each button has its own Lucide icon that never changes
270	- Avoids all Lucide resizing issues
271	
272	### 2. Positioning Context
273	- Component uses **padding: 16px 24px 0 24px** to match filter-counter
274	- Toggle buttons use **absolute positioning** within header wrapper
275	- Collapsed label positioned absolutely relative to component
276	
277	### 3. Critical CSS Rules
278	- **overflow: hidden** on content container is needed for collapse animation
279	- **z-index** hierarchy: collapsed button (20) > collapsed label (11) > base toggle (10)
280	- **Shadow space**: 10px bottom padding on severity-boxes-row
281	
282	### 4. Common Issues & Solutions
283	- **Icons not visible**: Ensure `stroke` property is set, not just `color`
284	- **Shadow clipping**: Add padding to container, not margin
285	- **Button positioning**: Use absolute positioning for precise control
286	- **Collapsed button hidden**: Check display property isn't overridden
287	
288	### 5. Color Reference
289	- Default icon color: #A8AEB3
290	- Hover color: #F26419
291	- Text color: rgba(37, 53, 65, 0.9)
292	
293	### 6. Size Reference
294	- Expanded button: 28Ã—28px
295	- Expanded icon: 28Ã—28px
296	- Collapsed button: 15Ã—15px
297	- Collapsed icon: 10.5Ã—10.5px
298	- Header font: 24pt
299	
300	### 7. Implementation Order
301	1. Update HTML with two buttons
302	2. Add CSS for both button states
303	3. Update JavaScript to remove icon switching
304	4. Test collapse/expand functionality
305	5. Fine-tune positioning
306	
307	## For Violation Details Implementation
308	Apply the same pattern:
309	1. Create two buttons (expanded/collapsed)
310	2. Use CSS to show/hide based on `.violation-details-component.collapsed`
311	3. Remove any icon switching from JavaScript
312	4. Ensure proper z-index layering
313	5. Match the toggle button sizes to other components (28Ã—28px expanded)

